# Agents skills

Every conversation or development cycle must create or update skills inside `.agents/skills`.

## Naming

```text
.agents/skills/develop-module-[module-name]/
```

## Scope

This applies only to major modules.

## Folder layout (progressive disclosure)

### Simple skill

```text
develop-module-checkout/
└── SKILL.md
```

### Complex skill (module with sub-parts) — prefer this for one source of truth

```text
develop-module-checkout/
├── SKILL.md                 # router + shared map + must-knows (<500 lines)
└── references/
    ├── payment.md           # sub-part detail
    ├── cart.md
    └── fulfillment.md
```

Optional when needed: `scripts/`, `assets/`.

Do **not** split one module into many skills that copy the same map. Keep one skill folder; put sub-part detail in `references/`.

## Guidelines

- Keep skills high-level: file locations and must-knows, not deep implementation dumps. Add anything useful that prevents early context thrashing.
- Use english language.
- If the module involves an external service or multiple codebases, mention only the project path or project name, and briefly describe its purpose for this module.
- Keep links **one level deep** from `SKILL.md` (e.g. `references/payment.md`). No reference → reference chains.
- In `SKILL.md`, say **when** to open each reference (e.g. "If touching payment, read `references/payment.md`"). Do not paste the same facts into both `SKILL.md` and `references/`.

## Required `SKILL.md` structure

```markdown
## When to Use

## Key locations

## References

## Learned user preferences

## Learned Workspace Facts
```

In `## References`, list each file under `references/` with when to open it. Example:

```markdown
## References

- [payment.md](references/payment.md) — when changing payment flow or providers
- [cart.md](references/cart.md) — when changing cart or line items
```

If there are no `references/` files yet, write `- (none)` and add entries when files are created.

Optional sections when useful: `Overview`, `External projects`, `Gotchas`.

## `references/` files

Use for sub-part maps, long schemas, edge cases, or domain variants. Each file should be self-contained for that sub-part. Keep the `## References` list in `SKILL.md` in sync with this folder.
